ssential for emerging neighborhoods or post-crisis recovery periods. The framework supports multi-horizon forecasting with regime trajectory prediction, enabling long-term planning under anticipated urban shifts. Impact-wise, RaCaST-GNP enables law enforcement and city planners to anticipate not just crime hotspots, but *regime transitions* that signal systemic changes in public safety dynamics. It offers a new paradigm in trustworthy AI: systems that adapt to structural breaks rather than fail under them.",
